We have an issue with fruit flies or whatever you want to call the little buggers!
I've set out the traps you can buy at store (don't waist your money on them!)
and I've even set out coffee with French vanilla creamer and dish soap (FYI this works fairly well but you have coffee cups sitting around.)
I wanted something I did not have to do anything with and these work.
You can turn them on and off.
I leave mine on.
They really work mostly at night as the bugs are attracted to the light in them.
You do have to clean them now and then.
Easy to do.
Just take off front cover and wipe off metal peice inside.
NOTE: Unplug them first!
Yeah I know most of you know this but just in case!
LOL.
So I now have two in my kitchen area, one in each bathroom, one in my office because for some reason I find the little buggers in there!
I had a few extras so I also have them in other rooms also.
I now might see one fruit fly now and then where before I'd sit down and have them flying in my face.
That's totally annoying!
So these definitely help.

The drone finds its "balance" during the first few seconds that it has power.
If it's leaning one way or the other during this time it will tend to wander.
I also found that putting it in headless mode makes it easier to fly for newbies like myself.
This drone is very durable and there are replacement parts available on Amazon that won't break the bank.
